Claims CLAIMS WHAT is CLAIMED is: 1. A method comprising: receiving an indication that a first intermediate node of a network is to be removed from service; based at least in part on the indication, refraining from sending new connection requests to the first intermediate node; based at least in part on the indication, identifying a client device having an existing connection through the first intermediate node; sending a request to the client device to prompt the client device to establish a new connection; determining that the new connection has been established such that the new connection flows through a second intermediate node of the network; and removing the first intermediate node from service based at least in part on the new connection being established. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein: the request to establish the new connection is sent to each client device of multiple client devices that have existing connections through the first intermediate node, and removing the first intermediate node from service is based at least in part on determining that each one of the multiple client devices have established new connections through other intermediate nodes of the network that are different from the first intermediate node. 3. The method of claim 1 or 2, wherein the request to establish the new connection includes at least one of a hostname or an internet protocol (IP) address that is associated with the second intermediate node. 4. The method of any of claims 1 to 3, further comprising one of: updating the first intermediate node with a new version of software while the first intermediate node is removed from service; or deploying a new intermediate node to replace the first intermediate node based at least in part on the first intermediate node being removed from service. 5. The method of any of claims 1 to 4, further comprising: receiving, at the network, a request to establish the new connection for use by the client device; and establishing the new connection between the client device and the second intermediate node based at least in part on the indication. 6. The method of claim 5, further comprising removing, by the client device and at least partially responsive to the new connection being established, the existing connection through the first intermediate node. 7. The method of any of claims 1 to 6, wherein the network is a cloud-based virtual private network (VPN) headend service and the first intermediate node is at least one of a load balancer node, a proxy node, or a headend node of the VPN headend service. 8. The method of any of claims 1 to 7, wherein the first intermediate node is associated with a first datacenter and the second intermediate node is associated with a second datacenter, the second datacenter located in a different geographical location than the first datacenter. 9. A system comprising: one or more processors; and one or more non-transitory computer-readable media storing instructions that, when executed, cause the one or more processors to perform operations comprising: receiving, at a controller of a cloud-based virtual private network (VPN) service, an indication that a first headend node of the cloud-based VPN service is to be removed from service; causing, by the controller and based at least in part on the indication, a proxy node of the cloud-based VPN service to refrain from establishing new connections with the first headend node; causing, by the controller and based at least in part on the indication, the first headend node to send a reconnect request to a client device that is connected to the first headend node; 

 determining, by the controller, that the client device has reconnected to a second headend node of the cloud-based VPN service that is different than the first headend node; and based at least in part on the client device being reconnected to the second headend node, removing the first headend node from the cloud-based VPN service. 10. The system of claim 9, wherein: the reconnect request is sent to each client device of multiple client devices that are connected to the first headend node, and removing the first headend node from service is based at least in part on determining that each one of the multiple client devices have reconnected to a different headend node than the first headend node. 11. The system of claim 9 or 10, wherein the reconnect request includes at least one of a hostname or an internet protocol (IP) address that is associated with the second headend node. 12. The system of any of claims 9 to 11, the operations further comprising one of: updating the first headend node with a new version of software while the first headend node is removed from service; or deploying a new headend node to replace the first headend node based at least in part on the first headend node being removed from service. 13. The system of any of claims 9 to 12, the operations further comprising: receiving, at the proxy node, a request to establish a new connection for use by the client device; and establishing, by the proxy node, the new connection between the client device and the second headend node based at least in part on the controller causing the proxy node to refrain from establishing new connection with the first headend node. 14. The system of claim 13, the operations further comprising removing, by the client device and at least partially responsive to the proxy node establishing the new connection, a prior connection between the client device and the first headend node. 15. The system of any of claims 9 to 14, wherein the first headend node is associated with a first datacenter and the second headend node is associated with a second datacenter, the second datacenter located in a different geographical location than the first datacenter. 16. A method comprising: receiving an indication that a first proxy node of a cloud-based VPN service is to be removed from service; based at least in part on the indication, causing a load balancer node of the cloud-based VPN service to refrain from sending new connection requests to the first proxy node; based at least in part on the indication, identifying a client device that is connected to a headend node of the cloud-based VPN service through the first proxy node; sending, to the client device, a request that the client device establish a new connection with the headend node; determining that the new connection has been established such that the client device is connected to the headend node through a second proxy node that is different than the first proxy node; and based at least in part on determining that the new connection has been established, removing the first proxy node from service. 17. The method of claim 16, wherein: the request to establish the new connection is sent to each client device of multiple client devices that are connected to the headend node through the first proxy node, and removing the first proxy node from service is based at least in part on determining that each one of the multiple client devices have reconnected to the headend node though a different proxy node than the first proxy node. 18. The method of claim 16 or 17, further comprising one of: updating the first proxy node with a new version of software while the first proxy node is removed from service; or deploying a new proxy node to replace the first proxy node based at least in part on the first proxy node being removed from service. 19. The method of any of claims 16 to 18, further comprising: receiving, at the load balancer node and from the client device, a request to establish the new connection with the headend node; and sending, by the load balancer node, the request to the second proxy node such that the new connection is established through the second proxy node instead of the first proxy node. 20. The method of any of claims 16 to 19, wherein identifying the client device comprises identifying multiple client devices that are connected to the headend node through the first proxy node. 21. An apparatus comprising: means for receiving an indication that a first intermediate node of a network is to be removed from service; means for refraining from sending new connection requests to the first intermediate node, based at least in part on the indication; means for identifying a client device having an existing connection through the first intermediate node, based at least in part on the indication; means for sending a request to the client device to prompt the client device to establish a new connection; means for determining that the new connection has been established such that the new connection flows through a second intermediate node of the network; and means for removing the first intermediate node from service based at least in part on the new connection being established. 22. The apparatus according to claim 21 further comprising means for implementing the method according to any of claims 2 to 8. 23. An apparatus comprising: means for receiving an indication that a first proxy node of a cloud-based VPN service is to be removed from service; means for causing, based at least in part on the indication, a load balancer node of the cloud-based VPN service to refrain from sending new connection requests to the first proxy node; 

 means for identifying, based at least in part on the indication, a client device that is connected to a headend node of the cloud-based VPN service through the first proxy node; means for sending, to the client device, a request that the client device establish a new connection with the headend node; means for determining that the new connection has been established such that the client device is connected to the headend node through a second proxy node that is different than the first proxy node; and means for removing the first proxy node from service, based at least in part on determining that the new connection has been established. 24. The apparatus according to claim 23 further comprising means for implementing the method according to any of claims 17 to 20. 25. A computer program, computer program product or computer readable medium comprising instructions which, when executed by a computer, cause the computer to carry out the steps of the method of any of claims 1 to 8 or 16 to 20.
